The paper deals with the stability of Kalman filtering over fading channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of probabilistic methods and random processes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.MA) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the study of temporal and spatial correlations in packet dropouts indicates a potential connection to signal processing (cs.SP).
